  ('patapsco-female-institute', 'Patapsco Female Institute', 'Ellicott City', '3655 Church Road', 'MD', 39.2694, -76.7978, 'other',
   'The haunted ruins of a 19th-century girls'' boarding school, now a historic park where ghostly apparitions of students in white gowns are regularly reported.',
   'Built in the 1830s by architect Charles Timus, the Patapsco Female Institute was a prestigious boarding school for girls aged 12 to 18. Several students reportedly died of pneumonia during harsh Maryland winters, and their spirits are said to still wander the grounds. Visitors have claimed to see apparitions of schoolgirls wearing long white gowns drifting through the ruins. One visitor, separated from her group, watched a young woman in a long gown walk out of the front doors, down the stone steps, and across the lawn before abruptly vanishing. Another witness saw what appeared to be a workman on top of the building — when she pointed him out, her companion saw nothing, and the figure had disappeared. The ghost known as Annie is the most frequently sighted, and the ruins are a popular stop on Ellicott City ghost tours.',
   1837, 'https://www.onlyinyourstate.com/experiences/maryland/haunted-town-md',
   '["https://www.onlyinyourstate.com/experiences/maryland/haunted-town-md","https://stephanieverni.com/2011/11/14/ellicott-city-steeped-in-ghost-lore/","http://ellicottcity.life/2018/01/15/top-4-most-haunted-ellicott-city/"]', 3),

  ('mt-ida-mansion', 'Mt. Ida', 'Ellicott City', '3691 Sarah''s Creek Drive', 'MD', 39.2688, -76.7972, 'mansion',
   'An 1828 mansion built for William Ellicott''s grandson, now the visitor center for Patapsco Female Institute Historic Park, haunted by the ghost of Miss Ida Tyson.',
   'Mt. Ida was built in 1828 for William Ellicott, grandson of the town''s co-founder Andrew Ellicott, and designed by architect Charles Timus. During the 1850s, Judge John Snowden Tyson and his family moved in, naming the mansion after his daughter Ida Tyson. Miss Ida lived in the house until she was 90 years old in the 1920s, and was known for keeping a ring of keys with her at all times. After her death, visitors and staff began hearing the distinctive jingling of keys as her ghost walks through the house. The phantom sounds are most commonly reported in the hallways and on the staircase. Miss Ida''s spirit is described as protective rather than menacing — a ''cleaning ghost'' who watches over her beloved home.',
   1828, 'https://midatlanticdaytrips.com/2022/09/walk-the-mile-with-the-most-ghosts-in-haunted-ellicott-city/',
   '["https://midatlanticdaytrips.com/2022/09/walk-the-mile-with-the-most-ghosts-in-haunted-ellicott-city/","https://stephanieverni.com/2011/11/14/ellicott-city-steeped-in-ghost-lore/"]', 2),

  ('wayside-inn-ellicott-city', 'The Wayside Inn', 'Ellicott City', '4344 Columbia Road', 'MD', 39.2635, -76.8027, 'hotel',
   'A Revolutionary War-era inn built around 1780, reportedly visited by George Washington and haunted by a woman whose perfume lingers in the hallways.',
   'The Wayside Inn was originally built around 1780 as a farmhouse on a profitable Ellicott City tobacco plantation. Local lore says the house harbored famous Revolutionary fighters passing through, including George Washington and John Quincy Adams. The farmhouse became an inn and public house in the early 1800s, and during the Civil War it may have provided rooms for Union soldiers garrisoned in town due to Ellicott City''s strategic railroad location. Guests and staff report the ghost of a woman who makes her presence known through disembodied footsteps, doors opening by themselves, and the scent of a woman''s perfume drifting through hallways when no one is present. One witness heard a door open followed by approaching footsteps, but found no one there. Known locally as "that house with the candles in the windows," many myths surround the famous candles, including the belief they signal the house is haunted.',
   1780, 'https://www.hauntedrooms.com/maryland/haunted-places/haunted-hotels/wayside-inn',
   '["https://www.hauntedrooms.com/maryland/haunted-places/haunted-hotels/wayside-inn","https://waysideinnmd.com/blog/haunted-ellicott-city/","https://www.marylandhauntedhouses.com/real-haunt/wayside-inn.html"]', 3),

