  ('teackle-mansion', 'Teackle Mansion', 'Princess Anne', '11736 Mansion Street', 'MD', 38.2006, -75.9237, 'mansion',
   'A grand Neoclassical mansion built in 1802, haunted by the ghost of Elizabeth Teackle who walks the second-story windows at night in a long white dress.',
   'Littleton Dennis Teackle built this grand Neoclassical mansion in 1802 in Princess Anne on Maryland''s Eastern Shore. The symmetrical five-part structure was modeled after a Scottish manor and was one of the finest homes on the Delmarva Peninsula. Elizabeth Teackle, Littleton''s wife, became deeply attached to the home, and the family''s financial ruin and loss of the property devastated her. At night, an apparition can be seen walking from one side of the second story to the other — many believe this is Elizabeth, still pacing the halls of her beloved home. A former tenant reported waking to see a woman in a long white dress who walked through his door and over to the window before vanishing. The Princess Anne ghost tour, considered the most disturbing on the Eastern Shore, includes the mansion as a key stop.',
   1802, 'https://www.wmdt.com/2018/10/haunted-delmarva-princess-anne/',
   '["https://www.wmdt.com/2018/10/haunted-delmarva-princess-anne/","https://chesapeakeghosts.com/ghost-walk-guide/"]', 2),

  ('old-jail-princess-anne', 'Old Princess Anne Jail', 'Princess Anne', '30888 Church Street', 'MD', 38.1994, -75.9244, 'prison',
   'A stone-walled jail rebuilt after prisoners burned the original, now a police station where officers and dispatchers report encounters with a frightening female apparition.',
   'The original jail in Princess Anne was burned down by escaping prisoners, so its replacement was constructed with 18-inch-thick stone walls to prevent another breakout. The building later became the town''s police department, but its violent past left an indelible mark. Dispatchers working late-night shifts have reported hearing cell doors slamming in the now-empty jail section. Police officers have had paranormal encounters throughout the building. In one chilling incident, a child visiting the station reported seeing a frightening, sick-looking woman in the building — in a part of the structure where no one was present. The apparition is believed to be a former inmate who died in custody. Somerset County is considered one of the most paranormally active areas on the Eastern Shore.',
   1870, 'https://www.wmdt.com/2018/10/haunted-delmarva-princess-anne/',
   '["https://www.wmdt.com/2018/10/haunted-delmarva-princess-anne/","https://chesapeakeghosts.com/ghost-walk-guide/"]', 2),

  ('old-white-marsh-church', 'Old White Marsh Church', 'Trappe', '9015 White Marsh Road', 'MD', 38.6556, -76.0583, 'cemetery',
   'Maryland''s oldest Episcopal church, established in 1655, where the ghost of Hanna — buried alive in the 1720s — still walks home from the cemetery.',
   'Old White Marsh Episcopal Church first opened in 1655, making it one of the oldest churches in Maryland. The most famous ghost story dates to the 1720s when the rector''s wife, Hanna, fell into a deep coma and was declared dead. She was buried in the church cemetery, but that night graverobbers came to steal the ring from her finger. When they cut her hand to remove the ring, Hanna awoke from her coma. She climbed out of the coffin and walked home to the rectory, shocking her grieving husband. Hanna lived for many more years after her premature burial, but locals say her ghost still makes that same walk — from the cemetery back toward the rectory — on dark nights. Witnesses have reported a pale woman in colonial dress moving silently along the path between the graveyard and the old church.',
   1655, 'https://discover.hubpages.com/literature/Haunted-EasternShoreGhostsSpooksSpiritsandHauntingsonMarylandsEastern-Shore',
   '["https://discover.hubpages.com/literature/Haunted-EasternShoreGhostsSpooksSpiritsandHauntingsonMarylandsEastern-Shore","https://chesapeakeghosts.com/the-eastern-shore-of-maryland-and-its-ghosts/"]', 2),

  ('high-street-cambridge', 'High Street Historic District', 'Cambridge', 'High Street', 'MD', 38.5634, -76.0789, 'other',
   'Called the most haunted street in America with 14 haunted sites in just two city blocks, including the tale of Bloody Henny and the LeCompte Curse.',
   'High Street in Cambridge has been called "the most haunted street in the country" by Eastern Shore ghost tour author Mindie Burgoyne, with 14 documented haunted sites packed into just two city blocks. Dorchester County, with Cambridge as its county seat, is considered the most paranormally active area on the Eastern Shore. The street''s most famous legend is Bloody Henny and the LeCompte Curse — a tale involving a powerful planter family and a gruesome revenge that echoes through generations. At nearby Christ Church cemetery, a yew tree more than 200 years old has roots encroaching on a headstone from 1817, and when the wind blows, the tree is said to sing. The concentration of hauntings is attributed to Cambridge''s violent colonial history, its role in the slave trade, and the maritime deaths along the Choptank River.',
   1684, 'https://chesapeakeghosts.com/the-eastern-shore-of-maryland-and-its-ghosts/',
   '["https://chesapeakeghosts.com/the-eastern-shore-of-maryland-and-its-ghosts/","https://whatsupmag.com/news/tales-ghosts-maryland-s-eastern-shore-reveal-history-imagination/","https://shorebread.com/2016/10/11/40-ghost-tours-october-marylands-eastern-shore/"]', 3),

  ('denton-old-jail', 'Old Denton Jail', 'Denton', '207 Market Street', 'MD', 38.8843, -75.8271, 'prison',
   'A 19th-century jail on Maryland''s Eastern Shore, believed to be haunted by the ghost of executed murderer Wish Sheppard.',
   'The Old Denton Jail is considered one of the most haunted sites on Maryland''s Eastern Shore. The building is believed to be haunted by the ghost of Wish Sheppard, a man who was executed for murder in the 19th century. Staff and visitors report significant paranormal activity including cell doors slamming shut, disembodied voices echoing through the stone corridors, and the feeling of being watched in the basement cells. The jail sits near two very old graveyards, and the area around Market Street has additional reports of hauntings connected to the ghosts of doctors, sailors, sea captains, and senators who lived in the surrounding historic homes. Denton is also known for the disturbing legend of the Town Dog Killer, whose spirit is said to wander the streets at night.',
   1860, 'https://chesapeakeghosts.com/ghost-walk-guide/',
